            "explanation": "4O Rima glottidis is present between the vocal folds of the larynx. The cavity of the larynx can be divided into upper, middle, and lower parts. Upper part: * It extends from the laryngeal inlet to the vestibular folds. * The laryngeal inlet is made of the upper edge of the epiglottis, aryepiglottic fold, arytenoids, and posterior commissure. * The vestibule is the region between the laryngeal inlet and the vestibular folds. Middle part: ¢ It extends from rima vestibuli to the rima glottidis. * Rima vestibuli is the aperture between the two vestibular folds. * Rima glottidis is the aperture between the two vocal folds. * Ventricle is the space bounded by rima vestibuli above and rima glottidis below. * Saccule is a pouch from the anterior end of the ventricle. It contains mucous glands. Lower part: * The lower part is also called the infraglottic cavity or subglottic cavity and extends from the vocal cords to the lower border of the cricoid cartilage.",
